  <article class="prose prose-slate max-w-none prose-a:text-blue-700 prose-a:underline">
    <h1>Updates</h1>
    <p class="kicker">Week-by-week log of what's changed at America's School Trust Library.</p>

    <p>
      The substrate behind this library — the booklet, the Sacred Compact white
      paper, the Vision essay, the per-state research — began in <strong>late February
      2026</strong>. The public library site at <a href="https://schooltrusts.net">schooltrusts.net</a>
      opened in <strong>early May 2026</strong>. This page is the running site-side log.
      Each week shows a one-line summary; click the week to expand for the daily detail.
    </p>

    <hr class="archival-divider" />

    <article class="weekly-update">
      <h2>Week of May 11, 2026</h2>
      <p class="weekly-summary">
        Newsroom Issue 3 shipped — first weekly entry sent via the new Buttondown pipeline
        from <code>newsroom@schooltrusts.net</code>, with the canonical web version landing at
        <a href="/newsroom/2026-05-13/">/newsroom/2026-05-13/</a>. Three substantive items from
        the period May 5–13, 2026: the federal BLM rescission of the 2024 Public Lands Rule,
        Minnesota's HF 3900 / SF 3593 constitutional amendment heading for the November ballot,
        and a $98.9 million wind-energy lease on state trust lands in Torrance County, New Mexico.
      </p>
